
REST:
	 is architectural style
	 stateless
	 requires HTTP
	 supports JSON, XML, HTML, CSV, plain text
	 easy documentation and easy to understand
	 efficient and faster
	 needs less bandwidth
	 less secure
	 Uses JAXRS API

SOAP:
	 XML based protocol itself
	 State or stateless
	 Can work with HTTP, SMPT(Simple Mailing Transfer Protocol) or FTP(File Transfer Protocol)
	 Only works with XML
	  Documentation is complex and hard to understand
     	 Slower than REST
     	 Needs more banwidth
     	 More secure
     	 Uses JAXWS API
     	 Platform and programming language independent

